18. A method for forming an optical waveguide filter according to claim 17 wherein the step of providing the optical fiber further comprises the steps of; 
a) forming the alternating arrangement of regions in the direction of light propagation by removing at least a portion of the cladding, and 
b) annealing the optical fiber to change the radius of curvature of at least one of the first or second interface of the cladding layer.
